#eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has increased the number of people allowed at religious gatherings over the Easter period, 250 people indoors and 500 outdoors. Ramaphosa addressed the nation on Tuesday. President Cyril Ramaphosa has increased the number of people who can gather to celebrate Easter. He made the decision following constructive meetings with several faith communities. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 "In recent weeks, we have held a consultation with faith communities to find mutually beneficial solutions to the challenges of managing large crowds at religious services," said the president. "Where the venue is too small to accommodate these numbers with appropriate social distancing, then no more than 50 percent of the capacity of the venue may be used." READ: Ramaphosa announces SA will remain on Alert Level 1 Ramaphosa says congregants should not gather outside their usual places of worship, and people must go home and not sleepover after services. ACDP leader Kenneth Meshoe says he is happy with an increase in the size of gatherings. President Cyril Ramaphosa has increased the number of people who can gather to celebrate Easter. ACDP leader Kenneth Meshoe says he's happy with an increase in the size of gatherings. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/7TURr9BV8Y SA will remain on Alert Level 1 Lockdown. The curfew will remain as is, while beaches, parks and dams will remain open. READ: COVID-19 Vaccine: Last Sisonke batch to arrive in April The sale of alcohol for off-site consumption will be prohibited on Friday, Saturday, Sunday and Monday, 2 to 5 April. Adjustments to the restrictions are as follows:   